We founded Valkiv after hearing the same frustrations again and again: people don’t trust their insurance companies, few understand their coverage, and even fewer know the true value of their assets.

The insurance industry(one of the world’s largest) has barely evolved, leaving millions dissatisfied and billions wasted each year.

In 2023, we partnered with Sweden’s top valuators to change this. We built tools to accurately value assets, an AI agent to simplify insurance policies, and a system to store and track belongings. Together, these form an ecosystem that brings clarity, transparency, and efficiency to insurance.

Our ambition is to partner globally with insurers, enabling faster claims, safer compensation, less fraud, and lower costs for the benefit of both companies and consumers.

Powerful Medical is redefining cardiovascular care with AI that interprets ECGs faster and more accurately than the world’s best cardiologists. Heart attacks cause 12 million deaths each year, and 50% are initially misdiagnosed, doubling mortality. Our AI detects acute heart attacks with twice the sensitivity and up to three hours earlier than the current standard of care, with the potential to reduce deaths by 75% within five years. Hospitals benefit through accurate STEMI triage, fewer false positives, and faster bed turnover. Beyond heart attacks, PMcardio is already certified for 38 additional ECG-based conditions, including arrhythmias, positioning it as the new AI standard for cardiovascular medicine. Since launch, 100,000 healthcare professionals have adopted PMcardio, detecting 36,000 heart attacks in H1/25 alone — saving or prolonging over 1,000 lives at first contact. With 30+ publications and 6,000 patients enrolled in an RCT, our clinical impact is rigorously validated.
shortDescription: Powerful Medical develops an AI-powered clinical assistant that supports healthcare professionals in diagnosing and personalizing treatment for cardiovascular diseases, leveraging advanced technologies to address critical challenges in modern medicine.

company_description:
Wemates introduces an innovative P2P risk-sharing platform, which operates purely as a technical intermediary, adeptly connecting individuals seeking equitable and transparent insurance alternatives.
In essence, we’re building a P2P risk-sharing network where a group of individuals with mutual interests or similar risk profiles pool their “premiums” together to insure against a risk. Our platform enables individuals with similar interests to share the risk between themselves, whether based on shared interests, community ties, or specific needs. Often these individuals are somehow connected, e.g. personally (friends), or through mutual business or other common criteria (e.g. possession or similar interests). These groups are then free to define their terms, set coverage limits, and even manage claims. That significantly diverges from traditional insurance
models by community-centric insurance ecosystem, utilizing decentralization and advanced technologies.
shortDescription: Wemates introduces an innovative P2P risk-sharing platform, which operates purely as a technical intermediary, adeptly connecting individuals seeking equitable and transparent insurance alternatives.

company_description: The single biggest gap in healthcare today is care coordination, even individuals spending €100k+ annually lack someone “watching their back, connecting the dots” as care remains fragmented and reactive. Our strength lies in combining AI, IoT, and geospatial technologies. With a growing database of over 50,000 labeled pest and disease images, TreeAiD offers AI-based image recognition and treatment recommendations aligned with government-approved guidelines. We also provide remote monitoring through LoRa-based IoT sensors, capturing soil salinity, moisture, pH, and nutrient data.
Greener Lab operates across both B2B and B2G sectors. Our solutions reduce diagnostic time by over 50% and cut OPEX by approx 30%.

company_description:
What does your company do?
Wormsensing develops and commercializes the world’s most sensitive and compact piezoceramic sensors to monitor vibration and deformation in real time. Our flagship product, Dragonfly®, enables unprecedented insight into the mechanical behavior of machines — from aerospace engines to manufacturing lines. Thanks to its ultra-thin format, plug & play design, and extreme sensitivity (1000× over legacy sensors), Dragonfly® captures what traditional sensors miss: subtle deformation signals at the source, even on moving or embedded parts. This data is then processed through our software stack, enabling predictive maintenance, quality control, and structural health monitoring across R&D, Industry 4.0, and OEM applications. With over 40 patents, strong traction (+110% YoY), and a proven in-house production capacity (2M units/year), Wormsensing bridges physical performance with digital intelligence — for a safer, smarter, more efficient industry.
prominent_investors: INNOVACOM, KBC Focus Fund, Cea investment
shortDescription: Wormsensing develops advanced vibration sensors and the Dragonfly platform, enabling precise acoustic pattern recognition and integrated physiological measurements for industries including aerospace, robotics, healthcare, automotive, and energy.
